From kevinushey at gmail.com  Fri Feb  7 19:50:03 2014
From: kevinushey at gmail.com (Kevin Ushey)
Date: Fri, 7 Feb 2014 10:50:03 -0800
Subject: [Rcpp-devel] no matching function for call in mzR on Mac after
 Rcpp 0.11.0 update
In-Reply-To: <1268550846.1747511.1391787987609.JavaMail.root@fhcrc.org>
References: <CAJXgQP2hHUrUGVn0X5OtKk2xqXw=p64UjsnwQQVmSyjaaqH5wg@mail.gmail.com>
 <1268550846.1747511.1391787987609.JavaMail.root@fhcrc.org>
Message-ID: <CAJXgQP0xY6Vp7P7YLAGFrwYtRZcW3aN=iDpNiLjDazrPb_e15g@mail.gmail.com>

Hi everyone,

I think I've gotten to the bottom of this. In Rcpp 0.10.6, the
Rcpp::Reference classes defined a default constructor; this default
constructor was left out in the reshuffle to Rcpp 0.11.0.

I'm not as sure why, but newer compilers are either 1) automatically
generating a default constructor, or 2) deciding one of the available
constructors is still suitable. This does not happen with
llvm-g++-4.2, hence the error.

I committed a hotfix to the installed version of Rcpp at BioC that
should fix build problems for now; but we can decide what the
appropriate solution in Rcpp is as well.

Cheers,
Kevin

